Package com.company.Annotation_2

package com.company.Annotation_2
  • Class
    Description
    AnimeCharacter
    The AnimeCharacter interface represents a blueprint for all anime characters, defining key methods like PowerLevel and currentForm that any implementing class must provide.
    AnnotationChecker
    The AnnotationChecker class provides methods to retrieve and display annotations associated with classes, fields, and methods of AnimeCharacter instances.
    CallMethod
    The CallMethod class provides functionality to invoke methods of AnimeCharacter objects using reflection.
    Gohan
    The Gohan class represents an Anime character from the Dragon Ball series.
    Goku
    The Goku class implements the AnimeCharacter interface and represents a character from anime with certain characteristics like name, current form, and power level.
    Main
    The Main class serves as the entry point for the application, demonstrating the usage of annotations and reflection with instances of AnimeCharacter.
    Preamble
     
    RunImmediately
    The RunImmediately annotation is used to indicate that a method or field should be executed or used immediately, and it can specify how many times the action should be performed.
    Trunks
    The Trunks class represents a character from the Anime world, implementing the AnimeCharacter interface.
    Vegeta
    The Vegeta class implements the AnimeCharacter interface and represents another iconic anime character.
    VeryImportant
    The VeryImportant annotation marks constructors or methods as being critical for the functionality of the class.
